article.story: NEW ORLEANS -- — Yaxel Lendeborg had 26 points in UAB's 78-67 victory over Tulane on Sunday. Lendeborg grabbed 12 rebounds and had three blocks for the Blazers (18-9, 10-4 American Athletic Conference). Efrem Johnson scored 13 points and added five rebounds and five assists. Javian Davis pitched in with 10 points and six rebounds. Kevin Cross finished with 18 points and four assists to pace the Green Wave (13-13, 4-10). Sion James added 13 points and Jaylen Forbes scored. Lendeborg scored 15 points in the second half to help UAB rally from a 38-37 halftime deficit. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
